2026 Regular Session
SENATE CONCURRENT RESOLUTION NO. 86
BY SENATOR LAMBERT
COMMENDATIONS. Commends and congratulates the French Settlement High School
girls basketball team upon winning the Division III Non-Select state championship.
1 A CONCURRENT RESOLUTION
2 To commend and congratulate the French Settlement High School girls basketball team on
3 winning the 2026 Louisiana High School Athletic Association Division III Non-
4 Select state championship.
5 WHEREAS, the members of the Louisiana legislature take great pride in recognizing
6 the achievements of student-athletes whose discipline, perseverance, and teamwork bring
7 honor to their schools and communities; and
8 WHEREAS, the French Settlement girls basketball team won its first state
9 championship in more than six decades when it defeated Westlake 44-34; and
10 WHEREAS, the victory marked the Lady Lions' first state championship since 1964,
11 restoring a tradition of excellence that has defined the French Settlement High School's
12 basketball program for decades; and
13 WHEREAS, the Lady Lions compiled an outstanding 31-3 record and demonstrated
14 resilience and determination throughout the season and postseason; and
15 WHEREAS, the team's belief and momentum were forged through several defining
16 moments during the season that ignited the team's confidence; and
17 WHEREAS, the Lady Lions championship season was guided by Head Coach Jake
18 Bourgeois, assistant coaches Josh Comeau, Edward Allison, and Jennifer Hull, managers
